Chaos address are almost always presented as one octal number and are
hardly ever presented as subnet/host, and NEVER NEVER NEVER in decimal.

Since you didn't supply a full example, I'm not sure if you are
proposing (with my modification), that MIT-OZ can be named as
	11406.CHAOS.MIT.EDU
or as
	11406.MIT.CHAOS
I would prefer the former since .MIT.EDU already exists (as would all
others) and the burden of mail is ONLY on .MIT.EDU and not on the entire
world.  Conversely, using .MIT.CHAOS would require a new top level
routing entry (.CHAOS) and those gateways would need to know a parallel
domain tree.

